  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this letter, Elizabeth Poole acknowledges a gift consisting of last year&apos;s Liberty Bell. Having been asked to &quot;contribute something for next year&apos;s volume,&quot; Elizabeth Poole sends a poem &quot;written some time back, but never published---I sent it to R. D. Webb who did not like it--- ...&quot; [The poem referred to, is: &quot;Prayer of the Captain&apos;s Clerk,&quot; by Elizabeth Poole, published in the Liberty Bell, 1849, p. 206-211.]</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The letter is accompanied by an envelope with the delivery address: Maria W. Chapman.</subfield>
  </datafield>
